(17, 'HTML Text Formatting Elements', '', 1, '&lt;h2 class=&quot;example&quot; style=&quot;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: normal; color: #444444; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Text Formatting&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;example&quot; style=&quot;width: auto; color: #000000; border: 1px solid #ebebeb; margin: 0px; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f1f1f1;&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;example_result notranslate&quot; style=&quot;padding: 4px; border-radius: 4px; width: auto; font-size: 17px; background-color: #ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This text is bold&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;This text is italic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is&amp;nbsp;&lt;sup&gt;superscript&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;h2 style=&quot;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: normal; color: red; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;hr style=&quot;color: #d4d4d4; height: 1px; border: 0px; clear: both; font-size: 14px; background-color: #d4d4d4;&quot; /&gt;\r\n&lt;h2 style=&quot;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;HTML Formatting Elements&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;In the previous chapter, you learned about HTML&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;styling&lt;/strong&gt;, using the HTML&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;style attribute&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;HTML also defines special&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;elements&lt;/strong&gt;, for defining text with a special&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;meaning&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: #404040; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;HTML uses elements like &am